02:22.058 --> 02:23.424
And I am gonna be right back

02:23.426 --> 02:25.627
to rescue your Italian leather.

02:25.629 --> 02:27.295
Thank you, babe.

02:27.297 --> 02:29.931
- Let's see the damage. Wow.
- Yeah, it got right in there.

02:29.933 --> 02:32.233
- Oh, is this yours?
- Oh, God.

02:32.235 --> 02:33.701
- This is... Oh.
- Yeah.

02:33.703 --> 02:36.671
- Are you a doctor?
- No, no, I'm not.

02:36.673 --> 02:39.240
I can have one here faster
than this baby can do 0 to 60.

02:39.242 --> 02:40.241
Why, is someone sick?

02:40.243 --> 02:44.712
Yeah. Me.

02:51.420 --> 02:53.254
Jeremiah,
is there something that I...

02:53.256 --> 02:57.892
would you take
my first patient?

02:57.894 --> 03:01.229
Why don't you want to work
with Mrs. small?

03:01.231 --> 03:03.765
Uh, she's a...
she's a geographical outlier

03:03.767 --> 03:05.300
on the schedule
Paige arranged for me.

03:05.302 --> 03:07.835
She's 4.6 Miles east
of Mr. adler, and, uh...

03:07.837 --> 03:10.204
Jeremiah...

03:10.206 --> 03:13.508
Are you afraid of handling
emotional women?

03:15.644 --> 03:19.113
It hasn't been within
the scope of my practice.

03:19.115 --> 03:21.616
I don't have the tools
to treat postpartum depression.

03:21.618 --> 03:23.451
Severe mood swings...

03:23.453 --> 03:25.553
Spells of anger towards others,
inability to be comforted.

03:25.555 --> 03:27.722
Yes, I know the symptoms.

03:27.724 --> 03:30.658
Jeremiah, you're not working
in a laboratory any more.

03:30.660 --> 03:33.928
You have to evolve to become
a part of this practice.

03:35.599 --> 03:38.633
Look, when I first started
at Hankmed,

03:38.635 --> 03:41.636
I struggled
with self-destructive patients.

03:41.638 --> 03:44.072
People who took foolish risks
with their own health

03:44.074 --> 03:46.941
and expected me
to bail them out.

03:46.943 --> 03:51.479
But I began to evolve.
And so can you.

03:51.481 --> 03:54.382
Maybe I can do this.

03:56.285 --> 03:58.319
If you come with me.

04:02.191 --> 04:06.260
So how can I help you, Sam?

04:06.262 --> 04:08.529
Doctor/patient confidentiality
applies to everything

04:08.531 --> 04:09.731
I tell you, right?

04:09.733 --> 04:11.766
Yeah, unless you plan
to commit a crime.

04:11.768 --> 04:13.701
On the contrary.

04:13.703 --> 04:16.170
I am not a rich socialite.

04:16.172 --> 04:18.906
I don't own a Ferrari.
This isn't even my dress.

04:18.908 --> 04:20.475
It's my disguise.

04:20.476 --> 04:23.177
You're working undercover?

04:23.179 --> 04:24.979
D.E.A.

04:24.981 --> 04:26.180
Here in the Hamptons?

04:26.182 --> 04:28.349
I didn't say it was a bad gig.

04:28.351 --> 04:29.450
But the hair extensions,

04:29.452 --> 04:31.285
the spanx,
the six-inch heels...

04:31.287 --> 04:33.454
Yes, being rich
is very hard work.

04:33.456 --> 04:36.190
Do you have any idea
how many squat thrusts it takes

04:36.192 --> 04:39.127
to burn off six ounces
of caviar?

04:39.129 --> 04:40.828
Right. Okay.

04:40.830 --> 04:44.198
You know, the fact
that you don't believe me

04:44.200 --> 04:45.700
is kind of a compliment.

04:45.702 --> 04:47.001
I didn't say
I don't believe you,

04:47.003 --> 04:48.503
it's just that
you don't look exactly...

04:48.505 --> 04:50.738
Henry Lawson, born August 23rd.

04:50.740 --> 04:52.840
I won't mention the year because
that just wouldn't be classy.

04:52.842 --> 04:55.309
Passaic high,
Northwestern university,

04:55.311 --> 04:56.778
mt. Sinai school
of medicine.

04:56.780 --> 04:58.980
Your brother's fiancee's father
is running for senate.

04:58.982 --> 05:01.783
Oh, and unlike your father,
you've never been arrested.

05:01.785 --> 05:04.585
Except for that time
in Atlantic city.

05:06.288 --> 05:09.023
I was 20 years old, and it was
a few hands of Blackjack.

05:09.025 --> 05:10.491
I know.

05:10.493 --> 05:12.160
Can we just talk about you?

05:12.162 --> 05:14.629
Great. Um...

05:17.433 --> 05:21.035
Okay, the first symptoms started
a couple weeks ago...

05:21.037 --> 05:23.705
headaches, trouble sleeping,
fatigue.

05:23.707 --> 05:26.140
My old partner started
the same way.

05:26.142 --> 05:27.909
And so did a lot of other agents
who worked meth cases

05:27.911 --> 05:29.811
back in the '90s.

05:29.813 --> 05:32.146
"Meth toxicity"
is what they called it.

05:32.148 --> 05:36.350
Most of them eventually
had to leave the agency,

05:36.352 --> 05:41.622
and a lot of 'em died,
including my partner.

05:41.624 --> 05:44.492
And you're wondering
if your symptoms are consistent

05:44.494 --> 05:45.793
with toxicity as well.

05:45.795 --> 05:49.397
I'm done wondering, Hank.
I just...

05:49.399 --> 05:51.733
I need to know how bad it is.

05:58.875 --> 06:03.544
♪ My independence went away

06:03.546 --> 06:08.316
♪ I didn't listen
when it said ♪

06:08.318 --> 06:10.218
